<div class="d-flex flex-column align-items-center my-5">
    <div class="stress-ball"></div>
    <p class="mt-3 text-muted">Click and hold the ball to squeeze your stress away.</p>
</div>

<style>
       
    /*In this code we are rrendering the stressball it is 300 px by 300px large. The border radius transforms this square into a circle as well, tells the cursor its a clickable element because the cursor is a pointer. Which lets users know it is interactable. Additonally the transition effect gives a transition on any animaiton applied to the elment.  */
    .stress-ball {
        width: 300px;
        height: 300px;
        background-color: #4b3b6b; 
        border-radius: 50%;
        box-shadow: 0 8px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        transition: transform 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.15s ease;
        cursor: pointer;
    }

    /* The active psuedo class activates when the element is clicked. In this case the stress ball grows by 1.5 units when clicked. and a shadow is given to it. */
        .stress-ball:active {
            transform: scale(0.85);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }
</style>
